%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{Pregunta}

\begin{block}{}
 ¿Pueden candidatos a ejecutivo \alert{subnacionales} transferir éxito electoral a sus compañeros candidatos a diputado federal en elecciones concurrentes?
\end{block}

\bigskip

 Efecto de arrastre entre departamentos \alert{no yuxtapuestos}---ni jerárquica ni transactualmente

\bigskip

Hay evidencia en Argentina (Jones 1997) y Brasil (Samuels 2000). \\ ¿También en México?

\bigskip
\pause

\begin{center}
  \begin{block}{Respuesta: \textbf{Sí}}
    El poder de arrastre de un buen (o mal) candidato a gobernador es \emph{igual o mayor} que el de un candidato a presidente
  \end{block}
\end{center}

}


\frame{\frametitle{Contenido}\tableofcontents}

\section{Coattail effects}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{El modelo electoral subyacente}

El desenlace de toda elección es producto de fuerzas largo- y corto-placistas (Converse 1966)

\bigskip

\parbox[c]{3.5cm}{de \textbf{largo plazo}:\\identidad partidista}                 ~~~~$\rightarrow$~~~~ \parbox[c]{3.5cm}{``voto normal'' \\ de un distrito}  \\[2ex]
\parbox[c]{3.5cm}{de \textbf{corto plazo}:\\calidad del candidato, \\economía...} ~~~~$\rightarrow$~~~~ \parbox[c]{3.5cm}{éstas desvían \\ de la normalidad}\\

}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{Arrastre presidencial = fuerza de corto plazo}

Un candidato excepcional entusiasma a muchos a sufragar también por sus copartidarios en la pista legislativa

\bigskip

Luego todo vuelve a la normalidad. \\ El ``pulso presidencial de las elecciones'' (Campbell 1991)

\begin{center}
\parbox[c]{6cm}{
 \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1,rotate=0]
  \draw[black,<->] (-.5,-1.5) -- node [above, sloped, black] {\footnotesize{voto diputados}}(-.5,1.5);
  \fill[green] (0,0) circle (1.5pt) node [below=2pt,black] {I};
  \fill[white] (1,0) circle (1.5pt) node [below=2pt,black] {P};
  \fill[green] (1,1) circle (1.5pt);
  \fill[green] (2,0) circle (1.5pt) node [below=2pt,black] {I};
  \fill[white] (3,0) circle (1.5pt) node [below=2pt,black] {P};
  \fill[green] (3,-1) circle (1.5pt);
  \fill[green] (4,0) circle (1.5pt) node [below=2pt,black] {I};
  \draw[red,->] (-.2,0) -- (4.5,0) node [right, black] {$t$};
 \end{tikzpicture}
}
$\leftarrow$ \footnotesize{voto normal}
\end{center}

}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{Efecto de arrastre presidencial  en EE.UU.}

Ferejohn y Calvert (1984): 

\bigskip

1869--1892:~~.91 (boletas fusionadas) \\
1932--1948:~~.56 \\
1952--1980:~~.31 \\

\begin{enumerate}
  \item No encontré una estimación para México
  \item ¿Es significativo también para gobernadores?
\end{enumerate}

}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{Arrastre gubernatorial}

    \begin{itemize}
      \item Fuerza de corto plazo mediada por la organización partidista $\rightarrow \Delta^+$ participación
      \item Pero requiere energía y recursos que agentes sólo usarán si esperan retornos
      \item ¿Un buen candidato a gobernador activa la maquinaria estatal: ¿hay efecto de derrame en elección de dip.\ fed.?
    \end{itemize}

\bigskip

\begin{block}{Evidencia}
Boyd (1986), Cox\&Munger (1989), Rosenstone\&Hansen (1993) ven efecto en \alert{participación} en EE.UU.\\
Ames (1994) ``reverse coattails'' en Brasil\\
Jones (1997) y Samuels (2000) medición directa con distinta métrica---núm.\ efectivo de partidos---en Argentina y Brasil 
\end{block}
 


}

\section{Un modelo para México, medición}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{México: laboratorio para estudiar arrastre}

\begin{center}
\textbf{Problema}: ¿cómo separas el efecto de arrastre \\ gubernatorial del presidencial?
\end{center}

\begin{center}
\resizebox{.9\columnwidth}{!}{
 \begin{small}
 \begin{tabular}{ll|cc|c}
    &   & \multicolumn{3}{l}{Congressional race concur-} \\
  \multicolumn{1}{c}{\textbf{A.~1979--2009}}  &   & \multicolumn{3}{l}{rent with presidential} \\
    &       &    no      &     yes    &    total   \\ \hline
 Congressional race concur- & no    & 153 (80\%) & 150 (94\%) & 303 (86\%) \\
 rent with gubernatorial    & yes   &  39 (20\%) &  10  (6\%) &  49 (14\%) \\ \hline
                            & total & 192 (100\%)& 160 (100\%)& 352 (100\%)\\
                            \\
  \multicolumn{1}{c}{\textbf{B.~1997--2009}}  &   &  \\
    &       &          &         &       \\ \hline
 Congressional race concur- & no    &  77 (80\%) &  57 (89\%) & 134 (84\%) \\
 rent with gubernatorial    & yes   &  19 (20\%) &   7 (11\%) &  26 (16\%) \\ \hline
                            & total &  96 (100\%)&  64 (100\%)& 160 (100\%)\\
 \end{tabular}
 \end{small}
}
\end{center}

Four-regime pooling tiene ventajas, permite separar \alert{dos efectos} de arrastre

}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{El caso de México}

    \begin{itemize}
      \item Analizo elecciones para diputados federales 1979--2009
      \item Límitación: unidad de análisis = estados
      \item Causalidad: no reelección ayuda, Gober $\rightarrow$ DipFed
      \item Desagrego coaliciones usando voto de sus miembros en la última elección que contendieron separados
      \item PCM, PSUM, PMS = PRD
    \end{itemize}

}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{La variable dependiente}

\begin{center}
 \begin{tabular}{cc}
  \includegraphics[width=4.25cm]{../graphs/dvpan.pdf} & \includegraphics[width=4.25cm]{../graphs/dvpri.pdf} \\
  \includegraphics[width=4.25cm]{../graphs/dvprd.pdf}
 \end{tabular}
\end{center}

}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{Modelo de regresión}

\footnotesize{
\begin{center}
%\resizebox{.85\columnwidth}{!}{
  \begin{eqnarray*}
    Dvote &=& \beta_0 + \beta_1 RecentDvote\\
          & & +\beta_2 GovOnlyConcurs + \beta_3 PresOnlyConcurs + \beta_4 Gov\&PresConcur\\
          & & +\beta_5 Gvote|GovOnlyConcurs + \beta_6 Gvote|Gov\&PresConcur\\
          & & +\beta_7 Pvote|GovOnlyConcurs + \beta_8 Pvote|Gov\&PresConcur\\
          & & + \texttt{controles}
  \end{eqnarray*}

\end{center}
\bigskip
Expectativas:
\begin{itemize}
  \item $\beta_1>0$ (voto normal)
  \item $\beta_2,\beta_3,\beta_4$ separan efecto de candidato mediocre de no-concurrencia \\ ``\textbf{umbral} de arrastre'' (cf. Chubb 1988)
  \item $\alert{\beta_5},\beta_6,\beta_7,\beta_8>0$ efecto marginal del voto ejecutivo \\ (\textbf{efecto neto} de arrastre)
                    \end{itemize}
}

}
